        quiz: [
            { question: 'What feature allows you to graphically control a Windows Server from another computer?', options: ['Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP)', 'Telnet', 'Secure Shell (SSH)', 'File Transfer Protocol (FTP)'], correctAnswer: 'Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP)', explanation: 'RDP provides a full graphical user interface for a remote machine.' },
            { question: 'On which TCP port does RDP typically operate?', options: ['80', '443', '22', '3389'], correctAnswer: '3389', explanation: 'The default port for RDP is 3389, which may need to be opened on a firewall.' },
            { question: 'What is the name of the client application used to connect to a Remote Desktop session in Windows?', options: ['mstsc.exe (Remote Desktop Connection)', 'rdp.exe', 'remote.exe', 'ssh.exe'], correctAnswer: 'mstsc.exe (Remote Desktop Connection)', explanation: 'mstsc.exe is the executable for the built-in Windows RDP client.' },
            { question: 'What is a major security risk when exposing RDP directly to the internet?', options: ['It slows down the server', 'It is vulnerable to brute-force password attacks', 'It uses too much bandwidth', 'It can cause the server to overheat'], correctAnswer: 'It is vulnerable to brute-force password attacks', explanation: 'Exposing RDP to the internet is highly discouraged; VPNs or RD Gateways should be used instead.' },
            { question: 'What is the command-line equivalent for managing a Linux server remotely?', options: ['RDP', 'Telnet', 'SSH', 'PowerShell'], correctAnswer: 'SSH', explanation: 'SSH (Secure Shell) provides a secure, encrypted command-line interface to a remote server.' },
            { question: 'What is the primary benefit of a Print Server?', options: ['It makes printers print faster', 'It allows centralized management of printers and print queues', 'It reduces the cost of ink', 'It allows you to print from the internet'], correctAnswer: 'It allows centralized management of printers and print queues', explanation: 'Administrators can manage all printers and jobs from one place, and users can easily find and install printers.' },
            { question: 'How does a client computer connect to a shared printer on a print server?', options: ['By plugging it in via USB', 'By adding it as a "network printer"', 'It connects automatically', 'By using Bluetooth'], correctAnswer: 'By adding it as a "network printer"', explanation: 'Users can browse the network for the shared printer and add it to their list of available printers.' },
            { question: 'What is a "print queue"?', options: ['The line of people waiting for the printer', 'A list of print jobs waiting to be printed', 'A type of printer cable', 'The printer\'s memory'], correctAnswer: 'A list of print jobs waiting to be printed', explanation: 'The print server manages the queue, sending jobs to the printer one by one.' },
            { question: 'If a print job is stuck in the queue, what service might you need to restart on the print server?', options: ['DHCP Client', 'DNS Server', 'Print Spooler', 'Windows Update'], correctAnswer: 'Print Spooler', explanation: 'The Print Spooler service manages print jobs. Restarting it can clear a stuck job.' },
            { question: 'What is a "printer driver"?', options: ['The person who delivers the printer', 'Software that allows the OS to communicate with the printer', 'The power cord for the printer', 'A license for the printer'], correctAnswer: 'Software that allows the OS to communicate with the printer', explanation: 'The print server holds the drivers, and clients often download them automatically when connecting to the shared printer.' },
            { question: 'What is a benefit of using a VPN to access a server with RDP?', options: ['It encrypts the connection, making it much more secure', 'It makes the connection faster', 'It bypasses the need for a password', 'It is free'], correctAnswer: 'It encrypts the connection, making it much more secure', explanation: 'A VPN creates a secure, private tunnel over the public internet to your network.' },
            { question: 'What is Windows Admin Center?', options: ['The old name for Control Panel', 'A command-line tool', 'A modern, browser-based tool for managing Windows Servers', 'A mobile app for server management'], correctAnswer: 'A modern, browser-based tool for managing Windows Servers', explanation: 'It provides a graphical interface for both local and remote server administration.' },
            { question: 'To enable Remote Desktop on a Windows Server, where do you go?', options: ['Device Manager', 'Server Manager > Local Server Properties', 'Control Panel > Printers', 'Task Manager'], correctAnswer: 'Server Manager > Local Server Properties', explanation: 'Remote Desktop is disabled by default and must be enabled in the server\'s properties.' },
            { question: 'What is "Network Level Authentication" (NLA) for RDP?', options: ['A lower level of security', 'An extra layer of security that authenticates the user before establishing a full session', 'A way to connect without a password', 'A feature for printing'], correctAnswer: 'An extra layer of security that authenticates the user before establishing a full session', explanation: 'NLA helps protect against denial-of-service attacks by completing authentication first.' },
            { question: 'What is the "UNC path" to a shared printer named "HPLaser" on a server named "FILESERV01"?', options: ['http://fileserv01/hplaser', 'C:\\HPLaser', '\\\\FILESERV01\\HPLaser', 'ftp://fileserv01/hplaser'], correctAnswer: '\\\\FILESERV01\\HPLaser', explanation: 'The Universal Naming Convention (UNC) path is the standard way to access shared resources on a Windows network.' },
            { question: 'What administrative task can you perform on a print queue?', options: ['Pause printing', 'Cancel a document', 'Restart a document', 'All of the above'], correctAnswer: 'All of the above', explanation: 'Administrators have full control over the documents in the print queue.' },
            { question: 'What is "PowerShell Remoting"?', options: ['A graphical remote tool', 'A way to run PowerShell commands on a remote computer', 'A chat application for administrators', 'A feature for shutting down remote computers'], correctAnswer: 'A way to run PowerShell commands on a remote computer', explanation: 'It is a powerful tool for automating administrative tasks across multiple servers.' },
            { question: 'Besides RDP, what is another common remote access technology that provides full graphical control?', options: ['VNC (Virtual Network Computing)', 'FTP', 'HTTP', 'SMB'], correctAnswer: 'VNC (Virtual Network Computing)', explanation: 'VNC is a cross-platform alternative to RDP.' },
            { question: 'When sharing a printer, what is an important consideration for a network with both 32-bit and 64-bit Windows clients?', options: ['It is not possible', 'You only need the 64-bit driver', 'You should install both 32-bit and 64-bit drivers on the server', 'You only need the 32-bit driver'], correctAnswer: 'You should install both 32-bit and 64-bit drivers on the server', explanation: 'Installing "Additional Drivers" on the server allows clients with different architectures to download the correct driver automatically.' },
            { question: 'What is a Remote Desktop Gateway (RD Gateway)?', options: ['A public Wi-Fi hotspot', 'A service that enables authorized remote users to connect to resources on an internal network from any internet-connected device', 'A type of firewall', 'A DNS server'], correctAnswer: 'A service that enables authorized remote users to connect to resources on an internal network from any internet-connected device', explanation: 'RD Gateway uses HTTPS to establish a secure, encrypted connection, which is safer than exposing RDP directly.' },
        ],
